Coerce PSM data to a data.frame

Source: R/functions-mzR.R
mzRident2dfr.Rd

A function to convert the identification data contained in an mzRident object (as defined in the mzR package) to a data.frame. Each row represents a scan, which can however be repeated several times if the PSM matches multiple proteins and/or contains two or more modifications.

as_data_frame(from)

Arguments

from

An object of class mzRident as defined in the mzR package.

Value

A data.frame

Details

This function implements the same funtionality as MSnbase::as(., "data.frame"). It as been renamed and isn't been exported to avoid conflicts and confusion. Ideally, the function in MSnbase might be moved to mzR and this package would re-use that one.

Author

Laurent Gatto

Examples

## find path to an mzIdentML file
f <- msdata::ident(full.names = TRUE, pattern = "TMT")
basename(f)

#> [1] "TMT_Erwinia_1uLSike_Top10HCD_isol2_45stepped_60min_01-20141210.mzid"

library("mzR")

#> Loading required package: Rcpp
x <- openIDfile(f)
x
